pageContext.claim: “Sometimes they'll say, 'Seven people from the White House.' They don't exist. It's a lie. They do it; they don't check. They don't do anything. They're really, really dishonest people.”
pageContext.analysis: Mainstream news organizations do not make up sources. Often Trump complains about articles in which the White House cooperated and provided officials to speak as long as they are not identified by name.
